Four people died and two were seriously injured in a car crash on the N2 near Kwambonambi on Wednesday morning. The KwaZulu Private Ambulance Service and police were on scene. According to a statement by the ambulance services, four people died before emergency services arrived on the scene. “Paramedics assessed the scene and found that one patient had sustained critical injuries and was entrapped in the vehicle, another patient had sustained serious injuries,” read the statement. The jaws of life were used to free the person who was trapped in the car. “The patient was treated and stabilised on scene before being transported to hospital for further treatment.”